{"overview":"A rigorous B minor fugue in five formal episode-and-entry cycles, distinguished by its exhaustive tour through six closely related keys via smooth diatonic pivot modulations and its climactic stretto culminating in a rare five-voice final cadence. The piece's most distinctive feature is the progressive compression of subject entries across the final section, where all voices converge in tight stretto before the texture expands outward into its densest sonority at the close.","cross_piece_tags":["fugue","counterpoint","circle_of_fifths","melancholic","tragic","dramatic","pedal_point","chromatic_mediant"]}
